---
import SpotlightCodeBlock from "./SpotlightCodeBlock";
---

<div class="xl:flex py-20 lg:py-28 gap-28">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mt-7 xl:mt-0 order-2 xl:order-1 flex-1">
    <SpotlightCodeBlock client:load />
  </div>

  <div class="xl:max-w-xl flex flex-col justify-center font-outfit order-1 xl:order-2">
    <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black">
      Works <span class="bg-clip-text text-transparent" style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(61, 4, 217, 1) 2%, rgba(114, 4, 217, 1) 55%, rgba(137, 10, 196, 1) 100%); -webkit-background-clip: text;">Seamlessly</span> with Your Workflow
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-8 text-lg">
      Pastoralist integrates perfectly into your development process. Run it as part of
      your CI/CD pipeline, include it in your pre-commit hooks, or use it manually
      whenever you need to update your dependency overrides.
    </p>

    <div class="flex gap-4 mt-8">
      <a href="/documentation/introduction">
        <button class="btn text-white border-0 hover:opacity-90" style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(61, 4, 217, 1) 2%, rgba(114, 4, 217, 1) 55%, rgba(137, 10, 196, 1) 100%);"> Get Started </button>
      </a>

      <a href="/documentation/setup">
        <button class="btn btn-outline"> View Setup Guide </button>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
